@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - vbsinst/VbsInstance
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired VbsInstance spec, tracked status,\nand delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetVbsInstance;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListVbsInstances using filters compartmentId,\nname, id;
:Create the OCI resource via CreateVbsInstance\nwhen no reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteVbsInstance with\nrequired via GetVbsInstance or\nListVbsInstances to DELETED confirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetVbsInstance or\nListVbsInstances until OCI reaches DELETED;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartmentId, name;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply ChangeVbsInstanceCompartment,\nUpdateVbsInstance only for mutable fields\ndefinedTags, displayName, freeformTags,\nisResourceUsageAgreementGranted (+1 more);
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=vbsinstance action=CREATED;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=vbsinstance action=UPDATED;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=vbsinstance action=DELETED when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Apply explicit follow-up semantics\ncreate=GetWorkRequest -> GetVbsInstance;\nupdate=GetWorkRequest -> GetVbsInstance;\ndelete=GetWorkRequest ->\nGetVbsInstance/ListVbsInstances confirm-delete;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: vbsinst
slug: vbsinstance
kind: VbsInstance
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=GetWorkRequest ->
GetVbsInstance; update=GetWorkRequest ->
GetVbsInstance; delete=GetWorkRequest ->
GetVbsInstance/ListVbsInstances confirm-delete
supported drift: definedTags, displayName,
freeformTags, isResourceUsageAgreementGranted
(+1 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, name
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_vbs_inst_vbs_instances filters
compartmentId, name, id; exact compartmentId
plus name unique match in ACTIVE, CREATING, or
UPDATING; duplicate matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, and DELETING as terminating; FAILED is
terminal and DELETED is only a
delete-confirmation target.
Create, update, and delete responses expose
work-request headers but do not return a
VbsInstance body. The runtime resumes through
GetWorkRequest, recovers the affected
VbsInstance OCID from work-request resources,
and then rereads GetVbsInstance before settling.
Pre-create reuse only runs when
spec.compartmentId and spec.name are present and
keeps exact compartmentId plus name matching
bounded to ACTIVE, CREATING, or UPDATING
summaries.
Only displayName,
isResourceUsageAgreementGranted,
resourceCompartmentId, freeformTags, and
definedTags reconcile in place; name remains
create-time identity and
ChangeVbsInstanceCompartment stays out of scope
for the published runtime.
The provider-only idcs_access_token header input
is intentionally not part of the published CRD
surface for VbsInstance.
Required status projection keeps VbsAccessUrl,
lifecycleDetails, and systemTags on the
published kind, and the runtime has no secret
side effects.
end note
@enduml
